{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gzweb/issues/66/comments/53243705.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gzweb/issues/66#comment-53243705"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gzweb/issues/66.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 66, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gzweb.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gzweb"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3e2fc3f2-dc25-453b-9792-943c743d9b40}ts=1609263"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gzweb", "full_name": "osrf/gzweb", "uuid": "{3e2fc3f2-dc25-453b-9792-943c743d9b40}"}, "title": "Configurable cameraview init pose"}, "content": {"raw": "@{557058:a0be01c9-8a7b-4d48-b235-0ae7bb093fb7} Yes, the initial camera pose from the launch file is used by `gzclient` but `gzweb` takes its initial camera parameters in the  `GZ3D.Scene.prototype.init`method which are currently hard coded to be: `this.defaultCameraPosition = new THREE.Vector3(0, -5, 5);`\\`", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><span class=\"ap-mention\" data-atlassian-id=\"557058:a0be01c9-8a7b-4d48-b235-0ae7bb093fb7\">@Kei Okada</span> Yes, the initial camera pose from the launch file is used by <code>gzclient</code> but <code>gzweb</code> takes its initial camera parameters in the  <code>GZ3D.Scene.prototype.init</code>method which are currently hard coded to be: <code>this.defaultCameraPosition = new THREE.Vector3(0, -5, 5);</code>`</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-08-01T14:00:48.630370+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ansar Khan", "uuid": "{3ff227d6-5bfd-442d-a735-d48b0eee7786}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3ff227d6-5bfd-442d-a735-d48b0eee7786%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3ff227d6-5bfd-442d-a735-d48b0eee7786%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/68874b8d9f304c07d0d47cffb3109dc3d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsAK-6.png"}}, "nickname": "Ansar Khan", "type"